                            <comment id="15057759" author="gnt" created="Tue, 15 Dec 2015 10:03:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure to understand exactly the desired behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I understand the patch correctly, the warning will only be issued when the same set of bundles fails for the second (or subsequent) time.&lt;br/&gt;
Won&apos;t that mean that if the deploy a set of bundle and never touch them again, you&apos;ll never see the warning ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15081340" author="rotty3000" created="Mon, 4 Jan 2016 16:44:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No that is not correct! This only limits the errors within a single &quot;iteration&quot; of the directory scanner.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To be more clear, the limit only applies to a single batch by the directory watcher. If the bundle fails again on a subsequent iteration it will still be reported.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
